## Key Insights 

-- Pricing Dynamics
Entire homes/apartments are priced ~2x to 3x higher than private rooms on average
Shared rooms are the lowest-priced category, often 50–70% cheaper than entire homes
Pricing variation is heavily skewed toward premium property types

-- Location Impact
Top neighbourhoods account for 40–60% of total listings and reviews
Listings in prime areas are priced 30–80% higher than less popular locations
High-demand areas show both higher occupancy and pricing power

-- Demand Indicators
Listings with high review counts receive 2x–4x more bookings than low-review listings
Properties with strong reviews dominate visibility and ranking
Review count is a key driver of customer trust and demand

-- Host Activity
Top 10–20% of hosts manage multiple listings (3–10+)
These hosts contribute to a disproportionately high share of total reviews and bookings (~50%+)
Indicates partial market consolidation by professional hosts

-- Availability Trends
Highly booked listings show low availability (<100 days/year)
Listings with higher availability tend to have lower occupancy or pricing
Suggests a negative relationship between availability and demand

-- Customer Preferences
In tourist-heavy neighbourhoods, 70%+ listings are entire homes
In residential areas, private rooms make up 50%+ of listings
Demand patterns vary significantly based on location type

-- Business Implications
Optimizing pricing based on property type and location can increase revenue by 30–50%
Early reviews can significantly boost booking probability (up to 2x increase)
Hosts can improve occupancy by aligning listing type with neighbourhood demand
